latestPosts.caption:
For the past two years, @sharduldonde, @taras84 and @saiyami have been coming to @utopiafarmstay to train for their @ironmantri 70.3 

They swim, cycle, run, and rest; things that aren’t always easy to do in the city. The air is cleaner, the weather cooler, and the pools are lakes, not chlorinated tanks. 

We’ve watched them push through injuries, juggle demanding schedules, question themselves and then come back stronger, each time. Every visit, we see them grow more determined, more resilient.

Yesterday, after a day of intense cycling (and falling), while we sat to have our evening chai, @taras84 called out and said “Look, we have a rainbow.” 

Before we knew it, there were two. One strong full rainbow. And above it, a lighter, double rainbow! 

As raindrops kissed our faces, we sat under the open sky, soaking in the Creator’s majestic painting in all its glory. The skies were changing colours so fast, even Instagram filters couldn’t compete. 

We spoke of fortunes, friendships, and futures. And at one point, @sharduldonde looked around and said, “This is real wealth.”

We couldn’t agree more. 

The chai. The rainbows. The conversations. The sunset. The love.

They say, you find a pot of gold at the end of a double rainbow.

Regardless of the double rainbow, we know we already hit gold. 

[Utopia Farmstay, Ironman 70.3, Simple living, Farm stay in Nashik, Sustainable travel, Wellness retreat India, Offbeat India, Saiyami Kher, Slow travel, Nature-inspired living, Mindful escapes]
